23/01/2006
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Miroslav Lajcak, EU special envoy for Montenegro, kicks off another visit to Podgorica Monday (23 January), to discuss the upcoming independence referendum with local officials. He plans to meet with representatives of the government and opposition, as well as with religious leaders and NGO officials. 
On Friday, Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic reiterated that he believes a compromise can be struck with the opposition regarding the terms and date of the referendum. Parliament is to hold an extraordinary session on 7 February to debate the proposed split from the union with Serbia. (Blic - 23/01/06; Beta - 22/01/06)
